description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen to join Basildon University Hospital Medical Education team. The Clinical Teaching Fellow / Clinical Fellow Critical Care Unit each is primarily to support the undergraduate teaching program for medical undergraduates across years one, two three, four, five and final year the critical care team in mainly Basildon CCU. The role will be split 50% medical education and 50% clinical in critical care unit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The main duties of the clinical teaching fellow post will be the implementation and integration of the medical curriculum, contributing to the departmental teaching program at undergraduate and postgraduate level, and helping create and deliver e-learning resources for ARU and UCL students. There will also be opportunity for developing research interests and contributing to the department’s research program and educational consultancy. The post holder is responsible for developing and supporting education and training of all medical trainees from undergraduate through to ST level.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
